    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-23T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="120"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112A/816a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-23T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6671. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_FPj1">Fuller</persName>, War Trade
                    Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 121 for <persName>Frothingham</persName>. It is almost essential for proper
                    control of enemy trade that American, French, and British lists be practically
                    identical. Am alarmed at number of names you have cabled as ineligible for our
                    enemy trading list. Request you reexamine facts concerning all names you have
                    described as ineligible and cable result of reexamination at earliest possible
                    moment. It is our informal understanding with British that supplements to
                    British list 41–A, including consolidation, will be made in accordance with
                    United States statute and our regulations for Latin America. Similar examination
                    and immediate report is necessary. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_FPj1"
                        >Fuller</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
